programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Jade Emperor orders Aquila and Sonar to come down to earth and assist the Kitchen God with the task. Meanwhile, Rascal the rat finds the royal edict in the Kitchen God’s house and considers it a good opportunity to change the destinies of his family and himself. Rascal hides the edict to keep other animals from seeing it while the Kitchen God sees through his ruse and tries to recapture the edict. They get into an argument and start to scramble for the edict. Just then, Aquila and Sonar break into the house and join the scramble for the royal edict immediately. In the midst of chaos, the royal edict drops into a censer and is burned into ashes.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Kitchen God, Rascal, and the two watchmen stand helplessly in front of the censer. Suddenly, a beam of golden light comes from the hearth and the royal edict floats up to the sky. The edict is made public and the news about the upcoming guardian tournament spreads like wildfire. The Kitchen God feels very remorseful for not keeping the secret. However, Aquila says that in that case they don’t need to worry about where to look for the competitors because all the masters will gather at Mount Tai from every corner of the village at that time.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is taking a stroll around the Marsh when all of a sudden a giant “owl” falls from the sky. Fearing that the scary bird would devour him, Joe hides himself behind a big rock. Bartle Bee passes by and finds something wrong about this furious “owl”. After a close examination, he discovers that this is not a bird but a paper kite. To fly the kite, Joe slides down a slope to help the kite gain altitude. The kite soars into the sky, taking Joe along on an exciting flight. At first, the fact that he’s ten feet off the ground frightens Joe Croaker. But as he manages to keep the kite under control, he finds himself fascinated by the midair adventure. Joe flies his “glider” and snatches the cheese from Cosmo, which makes the latter really angry. Joe gets completely carried away, when the kite flies into a desert scattered with cacti and becomes out of hand. In the end, Joe crashes in a huge cactus with his “glider”.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is casting about desperately for something to fill his empty stomach. Luckily for him, he finds some biscuits in a large can. So he jumps right into the can and gobbles up all the biscuits. But after the feast, the frog finds himself unable to get out of the can with an overstuffed belly. He tries all sorts of avenues and finally manages to hop up to the top. Suddenly, the can starts to roll down a slope. Joe freaks out inside the running can and cries for help, which is heard by Cosmo and Bartle Bee who happen to play nearby. They attempt to put a stop to the crazy can, but to no avail. At last, the can is halted on the edge of a cliff. Just when the Bartle Bee and his friends think they are safe, a rock comes running down, knocking the can down into the river. Fortunately enough, the three of them are saved by a large lotus leaf.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee finds a flowering plant in the forest. It is so good-looking that when Bartle Bee leaves, Joe Croaker brings it home and plants it in his back yard. The frog loves the plant and does not allow anyone except himself to touch it. But Cosmo still gets a nimble off one flower petal and the fly becomes extremely aggressive. Cosmo beats Joe Croaker up and makes the frog do his chores and give him massage.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo finds a discarded solar-powered toy car in the bush. He decides to keep it as a desirable toy. He shows off his new acquisition to Joe Croaker, who is immediately taken with the car as well. Joe Croaker seizes the car from Cosmo and tries to tug it home. As noon comes, the solar-powered car harnesses enough energy from the sun and starts to run on its own. Joe Croaker ties the car to a little tree, trying to keep it still. But fully charged with solar energy, the car breaks free of the restraint and takes Joe Croaker on an exciting road trip. Though a bit scared, Joe gets off on this wild car adventure. He snatches Cosmo’s cheese on the way. The car runs wild again and plunges into a pond, drowning Joe Croaker as well. Cosmo catches up, only to find his cheese cake gone under water.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo spots a paper boat on the stream. He picks two fine leaves as paddles and begins to go around in his boat. Flutterby is interested in the boat and she asks if she can join Cosmo. Cosmo refuses and Flutterby decides to make one boat on her own. She selects a large leaf and bends it into a boat.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Tiki chases their kite to Old Billy’s vegetable patch, and accidentally trample the vegetables. Although they try to correct the deed, but it just get worse. They try to avoid Old Billy in school and hesitate to apologize to him, for fear Old Billy will be angry. Briar tries to get Tiki and apologize to Old Billy. The old man tells them he’s going to the vegetable field to grow new vegetables. Briar and Tiki help him out. At last, they tell Old Billy the truth. The old man doesn’t get angry. Instead, he thinks they are responsible kids.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo doesn’t want to keep her old or broken toys, and asks her parents to buy her new ones. So she secretly throws away her old toys. When she visits Violet’s home, however, she finds out her friends treasure her toys very much, and remembers the good times she has spent with her toys. Then it rains. Luna-Loo quickly goes outside to find her toys with Violet but can’t find them. She’s feels regret. The next morning, she’s surprised to find out that all her toys are back. It turns out her mom picks up those toys, cleans and mends them. Luna-Loo realizes her mistake and thanks her mom. Violet and Vick come to Luna-Loo’s home and help her modify some old toys. Everyone is happy.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Summoning the Sun & The Frog Friends
programme.desc: Luna-Loo stays at Violet’s home for the night. They borrow a toy car from Vick powered by solar energy. However, the car runs out of power at night. They are disappointed to find out the sun has already set. They decide to summon the sun. First they to use some “magic spells”, then an ice cream to “entice” the sun to come out. They even mimic the sound of roosters to try to call for the sun. The sun never comes out. Instead, Violet’s parents are woken by the noise. Through a little experiment, they explain to the kids about solar rotation and the switch of night and day.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble discover that Old Billy’s office smells bad. They decide to help him get rid of the awful smell. They try to collect some fresh clean air from a flower field with bottles, and bring the air to the office. However, it’s hard to tell whether the fragrance is really inside the bottles. So they decide to use balloons to collect the scent. However, a little hedgehog accidentally pops the balloons when he tries to help them. Old Billy sees them and tells them that the stinky smell will go away if they keep good ventilation in the office.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is frightened upon spying what he believes to be a monster strolling around the pond. He soon realizes that the “monster” is actually a duck, but can’t work out that it’s in fact a toy duck. Assuming that this Rubber Ducky of Death is scheming to occupy his place, Joe Croaker flips out and decides to teach it a good lesson. He bullies the Rubber Ducky of Death until Bartle Bee sweeps it away. Bartle Bee is determined to rescue what he too, sadly, sees as a real—if unresponsive—duck. Joe gives chase to the two runaways, and they tangle with each other. During the confrontation, Bartle Bee accidentally gives the air-filled toy duck a prick with his sting, causing it to deflate and fly away. Still in the dark, Bartle Bee blames the disappearance of the poor little “creature” on Joe Croaker.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds a balloon dinosaur among the grass. The frog has no idea what he has discovered and he really panics at this “dinosaur” that is many times his own size. Joe Croaker begins to attack the balloon with pebbles he picks up from the ground. One of the pebbles bounces off the balloon and hits Bartle Bee’s honey jar on the ground. Though Joe Croaker tells Bartle Bee that he has nothing to do with the broken honey jar, the bee is smart enough to figure it out by himself.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo eats up all the food Joe Croaker has obtained, which puts the latter into a violate passion. And his mockery about Joe Croaker’s inability to fly adds fuel to fire. The hot-air balloons floating in the sky inspire the frog, who then manages to put together one with all the parts he collects from the garbage can. Flying with the ill-made balloon, Joe Croaker grabs the food from Cosmo and endeavors to catch the fly. But the balloon is too slow for Cosmo, so Joe plays dead to bamboozle Cosmo, who falls for it and ends up being caught. Just at that moment, the candle in the balloon exhausts itself. Both Joe Croaker and Cosmo fall to the ground, where the frog resumes his chase after his little foe.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a roly-poly toy when he is trying to get some candy near a dumpster. It’s a big smiling face doll. But the frog has no knowledge of what he is facing. He sees the roly-poly as a potential threat to him and the Marsh. Joe Croaker challenges the toy and attempts to take it down. The frog fails and finally he uses a rope to tie the roly-poly toy up.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: As the dung balls keep piling up, McBroom finds himself short of energy to get his work done all by himself. At Bartle Bee’s suggestion, he puts up a recruitment ad to look for someone to help him. The handsome benefits offered on this job allure many insects over, including Hercules Beetle, Snout Beetle and Bartle Bee. To select the best out of the three candidates, McBroom put them on a series of tests where Hercules Beetle stands out to win the position as McBroom’s assistant. Much to McBroom’s disappointment, however, his employee turns out to be quite lazy. So he has to give Hercules Beetle the sack and send him home.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Hammer the ox is an excellent blacksmith in his village but he only makes weapons. The village head persuades him to sell them at Carrotown because the market there is much larger. Hammer follows his advice and heads for Carrotown. Along the road, the ox tries to promote his weapons to an lumberjack and a watermelon farmer but they all mistake him for a robber and are scared to death.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper are walking through the forest. Unexpectedly, two hedgehogs stand in their way and plan to plunder their valuables. Velvet Touch throws two darts to them, which annoys the two robbers. They contract their bodies into two spiky balls and roll toward her. To protect Velvet Touch, Trapper rushes over and hits them with a long stick. He puts on an awesome Kung Fu show and transforms into Mad Wolf. After Trapper realizes he has spilt the beans, he deliberately loses out to hedgehogs and surrenders to them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: At night, three animals make a campfire and sit down for a rest. Velvet Touch keeps commending Hammer upon his braveness and complains about Trapper’s cowardice. Velvet Touch thinks Hammer can serve as a good bodyguard and persuades him to go with them together the next day. Hammer accepts her invitation with alacrity. The next morning, they continue on their way. The rabbit suggests to perform juggling acts to attract villagers over and sell Hammer’s weapons to them. Others nod their appreciation.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Artisan, the richest rooster in the world, writes a piece of calligraphy. All the officials curry favor with Artisan and praise him for creating such a masterpiece. However, the truth is that Artisan is an illiterate and the so-called calligraphy is just his scrawled handwritings. Artisan strolls to the backyard of his palace and sees a kite flying in the sky. On a whim, he decides to make a peerless kite by himself. He orders his attendant to choose the most expensive materials.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki’s Dancing Lesson & Mom and Me
programme.desc: Tiki admires Violet’s dancing. The kids all want Violet to teach them how to dance. Tiki goes to Violet’s home the next day. On his way there his friends tell him dancing is very difficult. He tries to learn some moves from Vick but he feel discouraged. He still continues to learn as Violet keeps encouraging him. But due to his nervousness, he steps on Luna-Loo many times while practicing. Luna-Loo tries to help him relax but none of the method works. Tiki dances in his own way and relaxes. He finally learns how to dance. He realizes he can’t just give up when others say it’s difficult.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Pink Racket & A Promising Flower
programme.desc: The cubs are playing badminton in the kindergarten. Herbert likes the pink racket. However, he overhears the others say the color pink is only for girls. So he does not dare to take the pink one, even though the one he uses is broken during the match. Then Old Billy joins them. The kids laugh at his floral shirt, but Old Billy doesn’t seem to care. Herbert understands he doesn’t need to pay too much attention to others’ opinions, and decides to use the pink racket.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: The cubs are rehearsing a show. At first, Babu acts well in his role. However, he becomes nervous when Warren and Luna-Loo come to watch the rehearsal. He forgets his lines, and can’t act. Babu thinks he didn’t practice enough but Luna-Loo thinks he has stage fright. He gives his role to Ernie Jo. Then Babu’s dad helps him to overcome his stage fright, and asks him to imagine the audience as fruits. At last, Babu doesn’t feel nervous anymore and acts well in the show.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Party at Violet’s & Got a Spare?
programme.desc: Violet invites her friends to her home, and has made proper arrangement. She thinks things will go smoothly. However, when her friends come to her house, they don’t want to follow her arrangements. They want to eat cakes and play with the ball. Violet doesn’t know what to do. Her father tells her that she should discuss with her friends about what to do. Violet listens to her friends’ opinions, and they all have fun.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. The cubs are busy helping Violet look for the chest, while Luna-Loo is invited to Ms. Lady Jane’s office, where she hears Violet’s words about how she cherishes the chest. Luna-Loo realizes what she has done is not right. Ms. Lady Jane comes in. She asks Luna-Loo to return a screwdriver to Vick, and tells her that even though she likes the screwdriver, she can’t keep it because she’s not the owner. Luna-Loo puts the chest back and makes a confession to her friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker picks up a bouncy ball among the grass and takes it home. This small ball bounces around in a way that the frog cannot control. Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. Just when the bird is about to swallow him, Bartle Bee and Flutterby show up. They distract the bird and save the bee’s life. In the end, the three of them put behind the grudge and become friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a slingshot in the Marsh. He soon realizes that it is a decent swing. The frog then takes a thorough examination of the slingshot. He is convinced that he can shoot some pebbles with this new toy he just found. The pebbles cause damage to the neighboring insects and Joe Croaker could not stop there. He finds a box of pushpins and starts to shoot them.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo brags about seeing a long train in front of Joe Croaker. The fly can see the world from above in the mid air but Joe Croaker cannot. This upsets the frog. Joe Croaker figures that if he climbs up to the top of the tree, he will be able to get a better view there. But sadly for Joe Croaker, on a long list of the things he can achieve, climbing isn’t one of them. Advised by Cosmo, Joe Croaker makes many failed attempts to climb up the tree. First he tries to do it by sticking the double-sided tape to his limbs, which results in a heavy fall from the tree. Then Cosmo fetches him a rope with a big hook that is intended to be attached to the tree and help Joe up. But it falls and almost has Cosmo crushed. In the end, on Bartle’s suggestion, Cosmo helps Joe Croaker build up a firm ladder which Joe Croaker takes to reach the top of the tree. But when up there, Joe realizes that he is afraid of heights!

programme.title: Moconomy - Economía y Finanzas
programme.desc: Moconomy muestra documentales sobre negocios y finanzas.

programme.title: Grjngo - Películas Del Oeste
programme.desc: Grjngo es la fuente de streaming más grande del mundo para las películas del oeste.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What is the most famous car movie of all time? Bullitt?… Vanishing point?... Gone in 60 seconds? Nice guesses, but in terms of influence and sheer popularity, Smokey and the Bandit stands above them all. Stacey takes a look at not only the cultural impact of Smokey and the Bandit, but also it’s most famous character… the black Trans Am. Then, it’s off for a test drive of Year One’s new Burt Reynolds Bandit edition Trans Am to see if it lives up to the true supercar status of the original. Finally, Stacey takes a look and shows you how to use, one of the most mysterious and versatile metal working tools out there… the English Wheel

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The “Rat Roaster” returns and Stacey finally reveals the kind of power plant that would have made this wild deuce roadster the fastest car in the valley in 1968. And if dual carbs, a blower and about 600 horsepower don’t get you going... maybe the fact that he’s stuffing a 5-speed manual transmission behind it, will! Then, Stacey digs into the Parts Bin to take a look at some of coolest products on the market to help you build your own special ride.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey not only brings the “Rat Roaster” ‘32 back in the shop, but he also takes it under the knife as he creates a very unique Dr Jekyll and Mr. Hyde style exhaust system and does some custom modifications to the frame to hide it all from the casual on-looker. If you are interested in taking your project and building it into something truly unique by thinking outside the box… this show will definitely encourage you to do that. Then, Stacey digs into some tips and tricks on how to set your vehicle up for storage for those times when your classic car or hot rod is going to be sitting for awhile unused.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: In the world of hot rodding, when gear heads gather around and start discussing their projects, invariably the conversation drifts into speculation of what the smallest thing is that you can successfully put a V8 engine in. Stacey pretty much puts an end to that speculation by building a V8 powered Barstool! It’s part go-cart… part garden tractor… part insane... and ALL hot rod, which of course is what Gearz is all about! If you like WILD… then you don’t want to miss this show! Then, Stacey dives into some Muffler Tech to show you what kind of mufflers there are on the market, and give you some tips that might help you make the right decision when the time comes to stick some cool mufflers on your machine.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: When it comes to classic hot-rod components, nothing gets people going like a multi-carb setup... the Tri-power. Long admired for their stellar performance and macho attitude, the tri-power has become a hard thing to find. So why find one? Why not build your own? Stacey walks you through the process of building your own tri-power out of old derelict parts. After that, he pulls out the big Mopar guns and shows what it takes to put together a six-pack. Then, Stacey gets down and dirty and shows you how to build some simple, ultra strong axle dollies by using some old scrap metal like the kind laying around your garage. Who said gearheads aren’t into recycling?

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The Banshee is back from paint and we're ready to answer the question… does it still look like a ’95 Miata? Has Stacey shown you how to create a completely different monster? Well, all we can say is the proof is in the paint and you are not going to believe how complete and affordable this transformation really is! Then, Stacey digs into the age-old question: Is it better to restore a car original, or modify it? The answer is up to you as he features a really clean ’68 Plymouth GTX… with some not-so-subtle modifications.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey pulls out the tools and starts working metal as he dives into the subject of what to do when your floors are gone… I mean literally gone…nothing there! It’s not as big of a problem as you may think! Stacey rolls in the Rat Roaster and shows you how to create solid metal floors from nothing. This show is loaded with tools and tech that will help you build anything from a small patch panel to a complete floor. While he’s at it, Stacey also covers seat selection and placement so you have a place to plant your seat when you get ready to roll down the street.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What do you get when you combine Armor All, Tony Stewart and Stacey David with an iconic vehicle like the Corvette? You get a really cool car called “Ol’ Smoke” and some lucky viewer is going to own it! That’s right, Stacey takes a brand-new ‘Vette' and shows you how to create your own 180+ MPH supercar for a fraction of the cost, using some aftermarket parts. How is that possible?... turbos baby!... and on this show Stacey shows you how to slap a pair of ‘em on the Corvette to run the horsepower numbers to over 600! programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Ol Smoke Corvette Brakes Wheels Tires
programme.desc: Ol’ Smoke is back as Stacey finishes up the transformation of a Brand-new ’08 Corvette, into a full-on super car capable of running with any Ferrari, Porsche, or Lamborghini. It’s a brake upgrade, along with wheels and tires and some custom airbrushing, to not only make the car even more unique, but to also get it ready for it’s new owner to enjoy. Then, Stacey takes Ol’ Smoke out and puts it through the paces showing once again that you can not only have fun building something cool, but also having just as much fun driving it when you are done. No doubt about it, somebody is going to get a special car when Armor All gives Ol’ Smoke away.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What is the nastiest project that everyone has to do eventually? That’s right… replacing old, worn out, nasty carpeting. Stacey rolls the Banshee back in the shop and shows you how to bring a very tired interior back to life with some tips and tricks that will help in replacing those old, worn out threads with some new ones. While we are on the subject of interiors, Stacey also digs into one of the best kept secrets in auto restoration… painting a dash and door panels. If you would like to make your dash and door panels look like new again in just a few hours… for very little money… and not have the paint flake off in a few weeks in big chunks, then this is the show you have to see!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey takes a look at one of the first aftermarket parts that became available to the public back in the day: the performance air filter… and man does it have an interesting story! From the lowly beginnings of fragile paper elements... to the massive, top secret facilities of industry powers like K&N, the air filter has a heritage that was born and bred on the race track! Then, Stacey digs into one of the neatest tools you’ll ever see and one that every metal worker should own… the Power Hammer. If you are interested in shaping metal and building your own panels, then you need to see this in action.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey borrows an ‘07 Jeep JK from a family and jumpstarts their project with the sole purpose of taking it to the next level. However, the real challenge is to build something the whole family will like and still be able to use on the street or off-road. If you’ve ever sat and stared at your project and tried to figure out what the heck to do next or what is the best thing to spend your time and money on… this show is the one to see!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey puts the finishing touches on the ’07 Jeep Wrangler with off-road bumpers, body armor, and lights... and builds a very capable off-road rig that is still civil enough to be driven every day. However, just before the Rhea family takes possession of their “new” Jeep, Stacey springs a little surprise on them… He enlists them to help him squeeze a little more performance and gas mileage out of the vehicle, just to prove that anybody can do it! On go the performance air intake, computer upgrades, synthetic oil, and even some slick new seat covers. If you have been reluctant to modify your vehicle because you didn’t think you had the ability…Think again! This show proves that anybody can be a gearhead and make their vehicle better in some way. So now you have no excuse to not be working on something!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey takes a well worn, ’73 Chevy pickup that was left for dead in the late 80’s, and starts bringing it back to life by upgrading the suspension and brakes. Not only is this a project that most anybody can do, but it is the start of a three-part series of the major steps that are involved in rebuilding a vehicle. With the way the economy is and the price of new vehicles today, this show demonstrates that there is a better option than buying something new…. bust your own knuckles and build it yourself! Then Stacey sits down with off-road racing legend Ivan Stewart to find out what makes him “the Ironman”.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey jumps back into the “KnuckleBuster” project, and deals with an area we can all relate to… a sick engine and transmission. But instead of getting rid of that old worn out vehicle, you can bring it back to life by stuffing in a new engine and transmission; Stacey walks you through the steps to show you just how easy this can be. But, you must be willing to bust your knuckles some and get your hands a little dirty! After that, Stacey puts on the gloves and shows you how to perform a little surgery on a tired rear-end to get the traction that only a locker can supply. Make sure to turn your head and cough!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Everybody knows that the area most prone to wear and tear on your vehicle is the interior. Well, that’s OK because today Stacey shows you how to dig into one and bring it back to life without spending a fortune. Whether you just need carpet, door panels, or a complete overhaul, this is something you can do with your own two hands if you are not afraid to get dirty. Then, it’s on to the place you spend most of your time… the seat! As Stacey goes through the steps of reupholstering your old rag-tag seat, you’ll see it can be made as good as new. If you are tired of driving around with an old ratty interior and don’t know what to do, this episode of GEARZ is for you!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What is the most famous car movie of all time? Bullitt?… Vanishing point?... Gone in 60 seconds? programme.desc: Determined to fly over Smurf village to catch a Smurf to take to the Wizard's Convention, Gargamel invokes his Book of Spells to help him. A series of funny flying machine mishaps occur and Gargamel is once more the laughing stock of the Wizard's Convention.

programme.title: All That Glitters Isn't Smurf
programme.desc: Gargamel captures ten Smurfs for his gold potion and Papa Smurf plans their escape. He lures the wily wizard into the woods with a mountain of fake gold while he uses the unwitting Azrael to help free the Smurfs.

programme.title: Dreamy's Pen Pals
programme.desc: When Dreamy decides to visit his friends, the Swoofs, Papa develops a potion to turn the Smurfs into alien-like creatures. But when the potion wears off to soon, Dreamy has to face the reality that the Swoofs do not exist. He is sad until a real alien arrives, returning Dreamy's letter that was delivered by mistake.

programme.title: The First Telesmurf
programme.desc: Papa Smurf pours a magic potion over the new Smurf-melon patch, which instantly grows and grows all over the village and forest. The Smurfs use the blossoms as a telephone, but before Gargamel can trace their voices, the flowers turn into melons and telesmurf is no more.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: While the Smurfs are in Africa they meet Prince Bakuri, who can change anything into gold with a magical statuette of a rhinoceros. But a greedy trader steals the amulet and Brainy...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In Egypt there is a cat pharaoh called Azrael and the name rings a bell with the Smurfs. As does the cruel taskmaster's name! Gargahotep wants to enslave the Smurfs to build a pyramid...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's growth potion is accidentally spilled on a Howlibird that grows into a giant creature. After much thought, Papa Smurf uses his anti-growth formula on the bird and soon it and the Smurf village return to normal.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A dragon terrorizes the Village of the Smurfs. To put the dragon to rest, the Smurfs must find the noted Chinese traveler. Fortunately, Papa Smurf is able to understand the strange customs of the stranger, and even to speak a few words.

programme.title: Foul Weather Smurf
programme.desc: Handy invents a weather machine that will allow the Smurfs to control their environment at will. Unfortunately, they cannot agree on whether it should rain or be sunny so the machine overloads and explodes.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Here goes Brainy Smurf again. When Baby Smurf gets lost whilst in the charge of Clumsy, Brainy insists that a trial be organized. How can poor Clumsy defend himself? How can Brainy forget that he was the one in charge of Baby Smurf originally? How will it all end?

programme.title: The Bad Place
programme.desc: What is this little moon coming from above? Why, it's a crater-pockmarked globe of mud inhabited by the Grimeys, a family of mud-splattering, mud-eating creatures from out there in the sky. Not all the Smurfs are enthusiastic about the visitors....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In his search for something new, Vanity dons a Gargamel-made magic hat that transforms his face into a mess. Through trickery, Papa Smurf gets the antidote from the wicked wizard and once more, Vanity is beautiful.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: How can the Smurfs save this future baby vulture? Right now, it's still in the egg and they must find a way of incubating the bird. And it just happens that the evil wizard Gargamel has found a way of changing himself into a bird to get at the Smurfs...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy gives Smurfette a pair of rose-colored glasses that are instrumental in luring her into Gargamel's clutches. Fortunately, a hungry giant comes visiting, tries the glasses on, which make Gargamel look very appetizing. As he chases the wizard, the Smurfette escapes.

programme.title: Smurfette's Lucky Star
programme.desc: Smurfette has chosen her lucky wishing star and it will remain hers forever... as long as she wishes for unselfish things. But Smurfette, with her badly chosen wishes, makes her star fall from the sky and Gargamel wants it...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A fierce wind carries the Smurfs' windmill away, with several Smurfs inside. Is Lazy Smurf really at fault or is an injustice being committed? Are the captive Smurfs going to be saved from the volcano's crater? Is Brainy going to smurf up his mouth for a moment?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Scruple And The Great Book Of Spells
programme.desc: When Scruple, helper to the evil Gargamel, finds the Great Book of Spells in his master's cellar, he asks for the power to be the world's most powerful wizard. This means trouble for the poor little Smurfs...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Simon is lost in the forest and in search of his parents. Simon is the son of a couple of giants. The Smurfs try to bring him home, but then Gargamel interrupts the party.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: None of the Smurfs seem to have time to play with the Smurflings. They go on a visit to Father Time and come across the River of Time, the great current that flows along majestically, carrying with it all the time in the world. And then an accident occurs, with untimely consequences...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh dear! Sassette has lost a tooth. Papa Smurf explains that if she puts her tooth under her pillow, the Mouse Fairy will bring her a present in the morning. But the next morning there is no present under the pillow. The Mouse Fairy has not been. She has been captured in one of Gargamel’s Smurf traps. And now the evil wizard is concocting a dreadful plan.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In the depths of the rain forest, the Smurfs meet with a headhunter who shrinks their skulls and changes them into pinhead idiots. Clumsy is able to escape, and matters come to a head.

programme.title: Mud-Wrestling Smurfs
programme.desc: The Wartmongers are draining Smurf River to make mud for their wrestling matches. Clumsy, who has been feeling like a loser at sports, becomes a hero when he must wrestle the Mad Maher as a distraction, enabling Papa and Hefty to break into the factory and destroy the mud making machine.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfs try to avoid contact with humans. But this time, Sassette is happy to be friends with a little witch called Melina, whose spells often end up in disaster. And anyway, are witches really human? At any rate, wizards such as Gargamel are.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In Baghdad the Magnificent, Clumsy Smurf meets the genie of lamp and, with his usual clumsiness, finds himself inside the magic object. Can he satisfy the Sultan's troublesome wish?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha disguises herself as the Golden Smurf Award to catch the Smurfs in order to use them as the main ingredient in her beauty cream. Vanity convinces her to try his recipe and before long, the wicked sorceress is covered with mud and sent careening over the hills into Gargamel's house.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs take Grandpa Smurf to the King's castle so that he can meet Peewit. But what with one thing and another (especially another), the Smurfs and Peewit are taken aboard a Viking long ship. The Vikings take Peewit to be their mythical Great Warrior, the one who is going to vanquish the Storm King. Can the Smurfs help Peewit out of his quandary?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The rain forest of South America is not a place where Vanity Smurf would like to spend his life. And then he starts dancing madly when he gets jungle fever. His dance will have strange results.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Directing the Smurfs to finish repairing the dam, Papa Smurf takes off on a herb-hunting expedition. While he is gone, Brainy causes havoc when he declares himself King and Papa Smurf returns just in time to save the dam from bursting.

programme.title: To Smurf A Thief
programme.desc: The Smurfs and Homnibus befriend an unfortunate boy who is forced to steal for his master. Soon, the evil thief is turned over to the magistrate and the boy is happy to live with Homnibus.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The starving Smurfs discover a cave that has a stash of frozen food inside guarded by an equally frozen troll who was imprisoned because of his greed by a magic diamond. As the Smurfs defrost the cave, Gargamel steals the food, but the magic diamond transforms him into an icy mass and the freed troll happily helps the Smurfs carry the food back to their village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clockwork Smurf is feeling so lonely that, out of compassion, Handy Smurf builds a female companion for him. The trouble is, Clockwork Smurfette does not know she's supposed to have eyes only for her mechanical counterpart, or that she should avoid Gargamel....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The boy from the wood and Laconia, the deaf-mute elf, ask Papa Smurf to celebrate their wedding. The Smurfs are getting the party ready, following the advice of the Smurfette, when Gargamel comes to put a spoke in their wheel.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wizard Gargamel creates an enticing Smurfette to lure the Smurfs into his castle. The Smurfette is thoroughly entranced with the little Smurfs, becomes one of them and together they cause Gargamel's wicked plan to backfire on him. With a magic spell Papa Smurf finally succeeds in making Smurfette look more Smurflike. It is no longer possible for Gargamel to dictate his evil orders through her powder box's mirror.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Everybody can make a mistake. Take Papa Smurf, for instance. His new perfume-enhancing spray makes a rose smell like a thousand roses...but due to a whole series of misadventures it also makes all the Smurfs cry, moved to tears by the slightest of pretexts. While they sob, bawl, wail moan and whimper, the evil wizard Gargamel does not stand still...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: If there is one thing that the evil sorceress Chlorhydris cannot abide, it is other people's happiness. The spectacle of the Smurfs' gentle and song-filled life gets Chlorhydsis' hackles up. She must destroy that tinkling laughter, smother those happy repartees... She plants the root of evil in the forest and soon, no Smurf is on speaking terms with another. Baby Smurf is the only one untouched...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A dragon terrorizes the Village of the Smurfs. To put the dragon to rest, the Smurfs must find the noted Chinese traveler. Fortunately, Papa Smurf is able to understand the strange customs of the stranger, and even to speak a few words.

programme.title: The Smurfomatic Smurfolator
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel still wants to destroy the Smurfs. This time, he sends on the forest the seeds of a creeping weed that is sure to entangle all the Smurfs... But Handy Smurf has devised a smurfomatic smurfolator...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It's not his fault. Clumsy Smurf never stops causing catastrophes, and even when Papa Smurf sends him to the forest on a single errand, he brings back a cloud of bad luck the shadow of which causes misfortune to anyone – or any Smurf – under it... Papa Smurf is going to need all his resources to find a cure: the silver lining that every dark cloud ought to have!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Village of the Smurfs is protected from intruders by a spell that makes it impossible for anyone to reach it if a Smurf does not lead them there. But this spell is going to lapse in a few hours and the evil wizard Gargamel is on the prowl.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: What a strange stone Clumsy has unearthed! In it, he can see events that are going to happen... Yet knowing part of the future sometimes brings bad luck!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: April Smurf's Day turns out to be not so funny when Gargamel dons a smurfberry bush disguise to capture the happy little Smurfs. Papa Smurf instructs Feathers to call the birds to attack the fake bush. After it is stripped, the captured Smurfs climb aboard Feathers and fly away.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Balthazar brings Denisa to Gargamel to baby-sit. But Gargamel loses Denisa in the wood and she and Sassette meet and become friends. Sassette and Denisa work together to free the Smurfs from Gargamel's stewpot, and prove you don't have to be big to be brave.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Being kind to animals brings unforeseen results for the Smurfs when they decide to bring a baby dinosaur back home... in its own era! This is the start of a series that spans space and time.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the Smurfs reach Mount Olympus, they meet with Zeus, who is not exactly showing Olympian calm. He is sending his timid son on an expedition to find the Golden Fleece. The Smurfs help...

programme.title: The World According To Smurflings
programme.desc: Mother Nature's not as she used to be, and now her back gives out on her. Who is going to carry on her chores while Grandpa Smurf is restoring her to health? She gives her magic wand to Nat, who is soon in touch with natural things. But there is trouble on the horizon, for the other Smurflings take it into their heads to help Nat.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Homnibus gives the Smurfs a dog that they name Puppy. The playful, normal-sized animal likes his new home, but Balthazar captures him, thinking that the Smurfs' magical secrets are in Puppy's collar. The Smurfs rescue the dog and Baby finds only music in the collar's locket.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Once a year, Greedy Smurf makes a special batch of Smurfberry candy. Every Smurf receives a whole year's provision of the smurfiest candy in the whole world. But can a Smurf keep his provision for a whole year? Can the Smurfette?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Jokey's surprise exploding packages have been changed by a spell. Picture the practical joker's discombobulating when he realises that all the surprises that he hands to unsuspecting Smurfs contain nothing but real gifts! No more ka-boom, no more jokes, no more fun! Plus the unenviable new position of Most Popular Smurf in the Village, surrounded by admirers begging for more presents...

programme.title: The Man In The Moon
programme.desc: Sick and tired of not being appreciated, the Man in the Moon quits his job and retires on Earth, to the Village of the Smurfs. The absence of a First Quarter Moon wreaks havoc in the customs of the Smurfs, and Mother Nature and Father Time get dragged in...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Tis The Season To Be Smurfy
programme.desc: This is Wild Smurf's first Christmas, and he's impressed by the decorations in the Village of the Smurfs. But Grandpa and Sassette are going to teach him the real meaning of Christmas when they help an old couple to live the most beautiful Christmas they've ever seen...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs discover a fountain of youth that is guarded by a wicked troll, who steals Papa Smurf's magic book. They convince Gargamel to help them and the greedy villain runs to get the water, but manages to fall in with the troll. As the two chase each other all over the countryside, the Smurfs are able to retrieve Papa Smurf's book.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: While out on a mischief-making mission to destroy the Smurfs' Happy Halloween party, Gargamel and Hogatha catch Lazy who has been accidentally turned red by Mother Nature. Papa and the Smurfs help Lazy escape while Mother Nature has Father Time help turn Lazy's red into blue just in time for the Halloween party.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh, sure, kickball (or smurfball, as they call it) is all right for a while. But it gets sort of boring after a few centuries. Now there's this new game that has been invented by a nondescript Smurf, a game where you hit a ball with a stick and send it into a gopher hole...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy Smurf is the one who fixes everything that needs mending in the Village of the Smurfs. But are his efforts really appreciated by the other Smurfs? Not at all. At least this is what Handy feels when he resolves to leave the Smurfs Village forever and live in the sea with Marina the Mermaid...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel the evil wizard is in trouble again. If he can't find an enormous amount of gold by sundown, all his possessions will be taken away from him. But the Smurfs are going to help their arch-enemy... Up to a point.

programme.title: Things That Go Smurf In The Night
programme.desc: When Snappy loses his Huggy teddy bear, he can't get to sleep despite Papa's efforts to convince him that teddy bears are magical and can take care of themselves. Gargamel stumbles into the Smurfs' village and Huggy returns as a giant bear to scare him away and save Snappy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel's theft of the Fairies' gold almost brings a state of war between the Fairies and the Smurfs.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un terrible gigante ayuda a Gargamel a capturar a los Pitufos para hacer una rica sopa, pero tendra que enfrentar a Papa Pitufo primero.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el hada de las flores aparece en el pueblo de los Pitufos, todos se enamoran de su encanto e inteligencia. Y pronto se daran cuenta de que se convertira en una especie de mama pitufo para todos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Habia Una Vez Una Luna Azul
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban cogiendole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve a por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que la acaban devolviendoles el bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel quiere crear un monstruo. Una criatura horrible y gigantesca, ¡un ser imponente que destruya a todos los Pitufos! Pero Gargamel comete un pequeno error y el resultado les dejara asombrados a su gato Azrael y a el.

programme.title: La Absopitufiasombrosa Maquina
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio inventa una maquina que hara que los Pitufos controlen el clima a su voluntad.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo no parece el mismo. Es educado, considerado, modesto y trata con cortesia a los demas Pitufos. A todos los Pitufos les preocupa que Pitufo Filosofo haya perdido todos los rasgos que conforman su personalidad. Y hacen bien en estar preocupados, ya que Filosofo ha sido victima de un artefacto denominado removedor de esencias que Escrupuloso, el aprendiz de Gargamel, esta utilizando... ¡Pero conseguiran recuperar la esencia de Filosofo!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando Pitufo Colerico pierde a su oso de peluche Huggy, no consigue dormir a pesar de los esfuerzos de Papa Pitufo por convencerle de que los osos de peluche son magicos y pueden cuidar de si mismos. Gargamel se tropieza con la Aldea Pitufa y Huggy regresa convertido en un oso gigante para espantarle y salvar a Pitufo Colerico.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Salomon el adivino posee un amuleto que permite a su portador conocer el futuro. Se lo entrega amablemente (quiza demasiado amablemente) a Pitufo Poeta que, desde ese momento, podra saber que sucedera a continuacion...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los malos modales pueden conllevar desventuras, tal como descubre Pitufo Colerico, uno de los Pitufitos, cuando una indignada tritona lo transforma en pez. ¡Y una flota de pescadores con redes se dirige hacia alli!

programme.title: Cosas Que Putifan En La Noche
programme.desc: Cuando Pitufo Colerico pierde a su oso de peluche Huggy, no consigue dormir a pesar de los esfuerzos de Papa Pitufo por convencerle de que los osos de peluche son magicos y pueden cuidar de si mismos. Gargamel se tropieza con la Aldea Pitufa y Huggy regresa convertido en un oso gigante para espantar y salvar a Pitufo Colerico.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Si hay algo que la malvada hechicera Clorhidris no puede soportar es la felicidad de las demas personas. Contemplar la vida de los Pitufos, llena de amabilidad y canciones, pone furiosa a Clorhidris. Debe destruir esas risas y ahogar esas felices conversaciones... Entonces, planta la raiz del mal en el bosque y, poco despues, todos los Pitufos dejan de hablarse. El unico que no se ha visto afectado es Bebe Pitufo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Baltasar lleva a Denisa con Gargamel para que este haga de canguro. Sin embargo, Gargamel pierde a Denisa en el bosque y esta se encuentra con Sasita y se hace amiga de ella. Sasita y Denisa colaboran para sacar a los Pitufos del caldero de Gargamel y demostrar que la valentia no es cuestion de tamano.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel lleva mucho tiempo intentando obtener oro a partir de los Pitufos. Esta vez, lo ha conseguido: ¡ha transformado a tres Pitufos en monedas de oro! ¿Conseguira Papa Pitufo devolverles su forma original? Pero ¿donde estan? No estan en la choza de Gargamel, ¡y es que dos ladrones le han robado sus preciosas monedas!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado primo del Rey, Malcolm, lo ha convertido en un ciervo negro para poder acabar con el y ponerle en su sala de trofeos. Los Pitufos iran a ayudar a su amigo y, tras devolver al Rey a su verdadera forma, Malcom acabara preso dentro del cuerpo del ciervo negro.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En lugar de insistir con su poesia, ya que nota que ninguno de los Pitufos la escucha, Pitufo Poeta decide escribir un libro. Y acaba de encontrar el material perfecto: un libro en blanco con una hermosa cubierta en el que comienza a verter su imaginacion. Entonces, en la aldea comienzan a suceder cosas extranas...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Tontin lleva una Rebotilla al pueblo, donde la pequena y adorable criatura se multiplicara y amenazara con comerse la nueva presa. Pitufo Armonia toca una cancion y las Rebotillas encandiladas le siguen en fila india hasta el bosque donde se juntaran a Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un extrano diablillo, que es todo un maestro de los juegos, desafia a los Pitufos en una competicion. Transforma a los Pitufitos en rigidas piezas de ajedrez y obliga a Pitufo Grunon, que nunca gana a ningun juego, a jugar para salvar las vidas de los Pitufitos. Pitufo Grunon va sintiendose mas seguro, realiza el movimiento correcto y consigue liberar a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan a las arenas rojas de Australia, Smoogle se encuentra con una tribu de sus ancestros. El y los Pitufos les ayudan a impedir que el malvado cazador Viejo Cindy los esclavice.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El Pitufidia de la Amistad es el momento del ano en el que, mas que nunca, los Pitufos demuestran su amabilidad con los demas. ¿Conseguira Clorhidris destruir esos buenos sentimientos? ¿Y como pueden los Pitufos encontrar una forma de cambiar las flechas de Cupido por algo mas agradable?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio inventa a Pituforobotin para que ayude a todos los Pitufos en sus labores, pero Filosofo lo reprograma para que abandone la Aldea Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Primera Navidad De Bebe Pitufo
programme.desc: La ilusion de Navidad se ve frustrada cuando Chlorhydris hechiza a San Nicolas para que no pueda repartir felicidad en Navidad. Afortunadamente, Papa Pitufo y los demas pitufos consiguen romper el hechizo y devolver la Navidad a su bosque.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Todo Lo Que Brilla No Es Pitufo
programme.desc: Gargamel captura a diez Pitufos para su pocima de oro y Papa Pitufo planea su rescate. Consigue atraer al malvado mago hasta el bosque con una montana de oro falso mientras utiliza al inconsciente gato para liberar a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Amigos De Sonador
programme.desc: Cuando Pitufo Sonador decide visitar a sus amigos, los Tufos, Papa Pitufo crea una pocion para transformar a los Pitufos en criaturas de aspecto alienigena. Sin embargo, los efectos de la pocion desaparecen demasiado pronto y Pitufo Sonador tiene que enfrentarse a la realidad de que los Tufos no existen. Esta triste hasta que llega un alienigena de verdad para devolver a Pitufo Sonador su carta, ya que la recibio por error.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Durante su estancia en Africa, los Pitufos conocen al principe Bakuri, que puede transformar cualquier cosa en oro gracias a una estatuilla magica con forma de rinoceronte. Pero un codicioso mercader roba el amuleto y a Pitufo Filosofo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En Egipto hay un faraon gato llamado Azrael, un nombre que resulta familiar a los Pitufos. ¡Y lo mismo sucede con el nombre del cruel capataz! Gargahotep quiere esclavizar a los Pitufos para construir una piramide...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un hechizo de Papa Pitufo sale mal y convierte a un ave en una espantosa criatura que aterroriza la Aldea Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un dragon aterroriza la Aldea Pitufa. Para vencer al dragon, los Pitufos deben encontrar al famoso viajero chino. Afortunadamente, Papa Pitufo es capaz de entender las peculiares costumbres del extranjero, e incluso de hablar algunas palabras en su idioma.

programme.title: La Absopitufiasombrosa Maquina
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio inventa una maquina que hara que los Pitufos controlen el clima a su voluntad.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Aqui viene de nuevo Pitufo Filosofo. Bebe Pitufo se pierde mientras estaba a cargo de Pitufo Torpe, y Pitufo Filosofo insiste en que es necesario celebrar un juicio. ¿Como podra defenderse el pobre Pitufo Torpe? ¿Y como ha omitido Pitufo Filosofo que el era originalmente el encargado de cuidar de Bebe Pitufo? ¿Como terminara este embrollo?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que es esa pequena luna que ha llegado del cielo? Es un globo de barro cubierto de crateres y habitado por los Lodosos, una familia de criaturas que vienen del cielo y comen y salpican barro. No todos los Pitufos demuestran entusiasmo por los visitantes...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En su busqueda de algo novedoso, Pitufo Vanidoso se pone un sombrero magico creado por Gargamel que le deja la cara hecha un adefesio. Mediante una argucia, Papa Pitufo consigue robarle el antidoto al malvado mago, logrando asi que Pitufo Vanidoso recupere su belleza.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Falso Y El Feo Plumaje
programme.desc: ¿Que pueden hacer los Pitufos para salvar a este futuro pollo de buitre? Ahora mismo, aun esta en el huevo y deben encontrar la forma de incubarlo. Y sucede que el malvado mago Gargamel ha encontrado una forma de transformarse en un ave para acercarse a los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Unos lentes rosados llegan a manos de Pitufina y resultan ser un sucio truco de Gargamel.

programme.title: La Estrella De La Suerte De Pitufina
programme.desc: Pitufina ha elegido su estrella de los deseos de la suerte y sera suya para siempre... mientras formule deseos que no sean egoistas. Pero Pitufina, con sus malas elecciones a la hora de hacer deseos, provoca que la estrella caiga del cielo y Gargamel quiere hacerse con ella...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La primavera provoca que todos los Pitufos esten compitiendo por el amor de Pitufina y Gargamel decide hechizarla para que le ayuda a capturarlos. Papa Pitufo toma cartas en el asunto y con la ayuda del despistado gato Azrael consigue darle la vuelta al plan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Escrupulo Y El Libro De Los Hechizos
programme.desc: Cuando Escrupuloso, el ayudante del malvado Gargamel, encuentra el Gran libro de hechizos en el sotano de su maestro, le pide poder para convertirse en el mago mas poderoso del mundo. Y esto supondra problemas para los pobres Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Simon se ha perdido en el bosque buscando a sus padres, una pareja de gigantes. Los Pitufos trataran de llevarlo de vuelta a su casa, pero gargamel aparecera una vez mas con no muy buenas intenciones.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Ninguno de los Pitufos parece tener tiempo para jugar con los Pitufitos. Deciden visitar a Padre Tiempo y llegan al Rio del Tiempo, la inmensa corriente que fluye majestuosamente, transportando todo el tiempo del mundo. Entonces, se produce un accidente que tendra inoportunas consecuencias...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Madre mia! A Sasita se le ha caido un diente. Papa Pitufo le explica que, si coloca el diente bajo la almohada, encontrara un obsequio del hada de los dientes al dia siguiente. Sin embargo, a la manana siguiente no hay ningun regalo debajo de la almohada. El hada de los dientes no ha acudido. Resulta que esta atrapada en una de las trampas de Gargamel. Y ahora, el malvado mago esta tramando un terrible plan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En las profundidades de la selva, los Pitufos se encuentran con un cazador de cabezas que les transforma en tontainas con la cabeza del tamano de un alfiler. Pitufo Torpe consigue escapar... y ahora le toca usar la cabeza.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las provisiones de comida de los Pitufos para el invierno se estropea y preparan un viaje hasta un lejano castillo en el que pueden refugiarse. Al principio, creen que el castillo esta embrujado, pero tras descubrir que solo se trata de un grupo de ratas, el propietario del castillo les obsequia comida en abundancia para el largo invierno.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos intentan evitar el contacto con los humanos. Esta vez, sin embargo, Sasita se ha hecho amiga de una pequena bruja llamada Melina, cuyos hechizos suelen acabar en desastre. De todas formas, ¿son las brujas realmente humanas? En cualquier caso, los brujos como Gargamel si que lo son.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren una Fuente de la Juventud cuidada por un espantoso Troll que roba el libro magico de Papa Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogatha se disfraza de premio de oro para observar a los Pitufos y capturarlos para sus ingredientes de belleza. Vanidoso acaba convenciendola de que pruebe su receta y acaba cubierta de barro de vuelta a casa de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llevan a Abuelo Pitufo al castillo del rey para que pueda conocer a Guillermo. Pero, entre una cosa y otra (sobre todo otra), los Pitufos y Guillermo acaban a bordo de una gran nave vikinga. Los vikingos creen que Guillermo es su mitico gran guerrero, aquel que derrotara al Rey Tormenta. ¿Podran los Pitufos ayudar a Guillermo a salir de este embrollo?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La jungla de Sudamerica no es precisamente el lugar en el que Pitufo Vanidoso querria pasar el resto de sus dias. Ademas, empieza a bailar como un poseso cuando contrae la fiebre tropical. Su danza tendra extranas consecuencias.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo deja a los Pitufos reparando la presa del pueblo mientras el se va de excursion en busqueda de hierbas para sus pociones. Mientras esta fuera, Pitufo Filosofo provoca un revuelo al declarase a si mismo Rey y Papa Pitufo regresa a tiempo para evitar que la presa se destruya.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos y Omnibus se hacen amigos de un desdichado joven cuyo maestro le obliga a robar. Pronto, el malvado ladron es entregado al magistrado y el joven esta encantado de irse a vivir con Omnibus.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos hambrientos descubren una cueva en donde se encuentra oculta comida congelada custodiada por un trol tambien congelado quien fue encarcelado debido a su avaricia por un diamante magico. Mientras los Pitufos descongelan la cueva Gargamel roba la comida, pero el diamante magico lo transforma en una masa helada y el trol liberado ayuda gustosamente a los Pitufos a cargar la comida de regreso a su aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Robotin se siente tan solo que, compadeciendose de el, Pitufo Carpintero le construye una companera. El problema es que PituforRobotinina no sabe que unicamente debe fijarse en su companero mecanico, o que debe evitar a Gargamel...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El chico del bosque y Laconia, la elfa muda y sorda, preguntan a Papa Pitufo que celebre su boda. Mientras los Pitufos preparan la fiesta bajo las ordenes de Pitufina, Gargamel hace acto de presencia.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado brujo Gargamel pide al mago Balthazar una receta para capturar a los pitufos. Implica secuestrar a la Madre Naturaleza para impedir la llegada de la Primavera. Por suerte, los pitufos salvan la situacion.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Todos pueden cometer errores. Incluso Papa Pitufo. Su nuevo pulverizador para potenciar el perfume hace que una rosa huela como un millar de ellas... pero, debido a una serie de desafortunados sucesos, tambien hace llorar a todos los Pitufos, que se deshacen en lagrimas a la minima. Mientras sollozan, berrean, se lamentan, gimen y lloriquean, el malvado mago Gargamel pasa a la accion...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Si hay algo que la malvada hechicera Clorhidris no puede soportar es la felicidad de las demas personas. Contemplar la vida de los Pitufos, llena de amabilidad y canciones, pone furiosa a Clorhidris. Debe destruir esas risas y ahogar esas felices conversaciones... Entonces, planta la raiz del mal en el bosque y, poco despues, todos los Pitufos dejan de hablarse. El unico que no se ha visto afectado es Bebe Pitufo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un dragon aterroriza la Aldea Pitufa. Para vencer al dragon, los Pitufos deben encontrar al famoso viajero chino. Afortunadamente, Papa Pitufo es capaz de entender las peculiares costumbres del extranjero, e incluso de hablar algunas palabras en su idioma.

programme.title: El Pitufador Pitufomatico
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel sigue queriendo destruir a los Pitufos. Esta vez, envia al bosque las semillas de una planta trepadora que enredara a todos los Pitufos. Sin embargo, Pitufo Carpintero ha ideado un Pitufador Pitufomatico...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: No es culpa suya. Pitufo Torpe nunca deja de provocar catastrofes, e incluso cuando Papa Pitufo le manda al bosque a hacer un recado, vuelve acompanado de una nube de mala suerte cuya sombra causa infortunios a cualquiera (o a cualquier Pitufo) que este bajo ella... Papa Pitufo tendra que echar mano de todos sus recursos para encontrar una cura ¡y encontrar la cara brillante que cada nube oscura deberia tener!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La Aldea Pitufa esta protegida de los intrusos gracias a un hechizo que impide que nadie pueda llegar hasta ella, salvo que un Pitufo le conduzca hasta alli. Sin embargo, el hechizo terminara en unas horas y el malvado mago Gargamel esta al acecho.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Pitufo Torpe ha desenterrado una extrana piedra! En ella, puede ver los eventos que van a suceder... ¡No obstante, conocer parte del futuro a veces trae mala suerte!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El Dia de los Inocentes Pitufo resulta no ser tan divertido cuando Gargamel se pone un disfraz de Pitufoarbusto para capturar al pequeno Pitufo Feliz. Papa Pitufo pide ayuda a Pitufopluma para que llame a los pajaros y ataquen al falso arbusto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Baltasar lleva a Denisa con Gargamel para que este haga de canguro. Sin embargo, Gargamel pierde a Denisa en el bosque y esta se encuentra con Sasita y se hace amiga de ella. Sasita y Denisa colaboran para sacar a los Pitufos del caldero de Gargamel y demostrar que la valentia no es cuestion de tamano.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuidar de los animales produce consecuencias inesperadas cuando los Pitufos deciden llevar a un bebe dinosaurio de vuelta a casa... ¡a su propia era! Este es el inicio de una serie de aventuras en las que recorreran el espacio y el tiempo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan al monte Olimpo, se encuentran con Zeus, que no demuestra precisamente tener calma olimpica. Va a enviar a su timido hijo en una expedicion para encontrar el vellocino de oro. Y los Pitufos le ayudaran...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Madre Naturaleza ya no es la que era, y ahora la espalda le esta dando problemas. ¿Quien se ocupara de sus tareas mientras Abuelo Pitufo la ayuda a recuperarse? Entrega su varita magica a Pitufo Natural, quien pronto pasa a estar en contacto con todo aquello que conforma la naturaleza. Sin embargo, los problemas asoman por el horizonte, ya que los demas Pitufitos estan decididos a ayudar a Pitufo Natural.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Omnibus regala a los Pitufos un perro al que llaman Puppy. A este animal jugueton y de tamano normal le gusta su nuevo hogar, pero Baltasar lo captura, creyendo que los secretos magicos de los Pitufos estan escondidos en el collar de Puppy. Los Pitufos rescatan al perro y lo unico que Bebe Pitufo encuentra en el medallon del collar es musica.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una vez al ano, Pitufo Goloso prepara un lote especial de caramelos de pitufrutas. Cada Pitufo recibe provisiones para un ano entero del dulce mas pitufantastico de todo el mundo. Pero ¿puede un Pitufo conseguir que sus provisiones le duren todo el ano? ¿Lo conseguira Pitufina?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un hechizo ha alterado las cajas sorpresa explosivas de Pitufo Bromista. Imagina la cara de desconcierto que se le queda a este guason cuando se da cuenta de que todas las sorpresas que entrega a otros incautos Pitufos en realidad contienen regalos. ¡Se acabaron las explosiones, las bromas y la diversion! Y a eso se le une su poco envidiable posicion como el Pitufo mas popular de la aldea, rodeado de admiradores que no cesan de pedirle mas obsequios...

programme.title: El Hombre De La Luna
programme.desc: Cansado y harto de que no le aprecien, el Hombre de la Luna deja su trabajo y se retira en la Tierra, en la Aldea Pitufa. La ausencia de la luna en cuarto creciente desata el caos en las costumbres de los Pitufos, y Madre Naturaleza y Padre Tiempo tambien se ven arrastrados por el embrollo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Es la primera Navidad de Pitufo Salvaje y esta impresionado por la decoracion de la Aldea Pitufa. Pero Abuelo Pitufo y Sasita van a ensenarle el autentico significado de la Navidad cuando ayudan a una pareja de ancianos a disfrutar de la Navidad mas hermosa que jamas hayan vivido...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren una Fuente de la Juventud cuidada por un espantoso Troll que roba el libro magico de Papa Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Durante una mision para interrumpir la fiesta de Halloween de los Pitufos, Gargamel y Hogatha consiguen capturar a Perezoso, el cual se ha vuelto rojo por un extrano capricho de la naturaleza. Papa Pitufo y los demas conseguiran liberar a Perezoso, y la Madre Naturaleza devolvera su color al pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El futbol (o pitufutbol, como ellos lo llaman) es un pasatiempo que esta bien para un rato. Sin embargo, se vuelve aburrido despues de algunos siglos. Ahora hay un nuevo juego, inventado por uno de los Pitufos: un juego en el que golpeas una bola con un palo y lo tienes que introducir en un agujero de topo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero es el encargado de arreglar todos los desperfectos en la Aldea Pitufa. Pero ¿valoran de verdad los demas Pitufos sus esfuerzos? De ningun modo. Al menos eso es lo que siente Pitufo Carpintero, quien decide abandonar la Aldea Pitufa para siempre e irse a vivir al mar con Marina, la sirena...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel vuelve a estar en problemas. Si no puede reunir una enorme cantidad de oro para el atardecer, le arrebataran todas sus posesiones. Sin embargo, los Pitufos van a ayudar a su archienemigo... hasta cierto punto.

programme.title: Cosas Que Putifan En La Noche
programme.desc: Cuando Pitufo Colerico pierde a su oso de peluche Huggy, no consigue dormir a pesar de los esfuerzos de Papa Pitufo por convencerle de que los osos de peluche son magicos y pueden cuidar de si mismos. Gargamel se tropieza con la Aldea Pitufa y Huggy regresa convertido en un oso gigante para espantar y salvar a Pitufo Colerico.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Todo Esta Bien Si Termina Bien
programme.desc: El robo del oro de las hadas por parte de Gargamel casi lleva a la guerra a los Pitufos con las hadas.

programme.title: 10 TIGERS of SHAOLIN -10 Tigres de Shaolin
programme.desc: Los famosos diez tigres de Kwangtung, una mujer y nueve hombres, derrotan a un hombre de la guerra local que está explotando a los aldeanos.

programme.title: Estrellas del Jaripeo
programme.desc: Emocionante serie original que presenta por primera vez en la televisión un torneo de peligrosas montas sobre gigantes y bravos toros, donde los mejores jinetes mexicanos arriesgan sus vidas para obtener este campeonato que se podrá ver en La Casa del Jaripeo.

programme.title: Ahí Viene el Toro
programme.sub-title: Torneo Tierra Caliente En Philadelphia, S01 E02 (CORTO)
programme.desc: El especialista en jaripeo, Luis de A, presenta un resumen con lo más destacado de las montas más peligrosas en las que valientes jinetes arriesgan la vida en jaripeos realizados en México, especialmente en Michoacán, y en la Unión Americana. Con base en su amplia experiencia, Luis de A analiza a detalle las montas más espectaculares, proporciona datos precisos, comenta la técnica y la dificultad de cada monta para que el espectador conozca todo lo que tiene que saber sobre este arriesgado deporte.

programme.title: Liga Mexicana de Jaripeo Profesional
programme.sub-title: Liga Mexicana de Jaripeo Profesional S03 E14
programme.desc: La Liga Mexicana de Jaripeo Profesional reúne lo mejor de este deporte extremo mexicano en una competencia sin precedentes. Jinetes de todo México arriesgan su vida montando los toros más poderosos. Morelia, Michoacán, es la sede de esta fiesta, disfrutaremos de las jugadas más impactantes y toda la esencia del deporte de los valientes. El peligro y la adrenalina nunca se habían sentido tan cerca.
